Officials deputed to visit houses for collecting details for revising the National Population Register should verify the documents in possession of families.The documents in possession of permanent residents of the State and officials should be checked, and it should be ensured that the details of family members enrolled in the NPR, deaths in the family, new births, and new members are properly recorded, District Collector Biju Prabhakar has said.The Aadhaar number of family members or their Aadhaar enrolment identification number, mobile phone number, and ration card number should be handed over to the officials collecting the details. The records necessary for detailed verification should be kept ready. â€“ Staff reporter